        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 2 at 2:55PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 255 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saragosa, or 23 miles southeast of Toyah, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Verhalen.

This includes Interstate 10 between mile markers 215 and 221.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
